# Drop unused columns
dropIND = c("Rank", "Category_11",  "Category_12",  "Category_13", "Category_14", "Category_15",  "Category_21",  "Category_22", "Category_23", "Category_24" ,"Category_25", "Category_31", "Category_32", "Category_33", "Category_34",  "New1", "New2", "New3","New4", "New5", "keyN")

df = df[ ,!(names(df) %in% drop)]

Step 3: Create Unique identifier - Indicator_ID and Indicator

# Create Indicator and Indicator_Id in df_IND
df_IND = df_IND %>% mutate(Display_Name_number = row_number())
df_IND = df_IND %>% mutate(Indicator_Id = paste(Display_Name_number, Dataset, answer, sep = "-"))
dropIND = c("Display_Name_number")
df_IND = df_IND[ ,!(names(df_IND) %in% dropIND)] #drop the auxiliary column created
df_IND = df_IND %>% mutate(Indicator = paste(Display_Name, Dataset, answer, sep = "-"))
# Create ID in df
df = df %>% mutate(Indicator = paste(question, dataset, answer, sep = "-"))
df = merge(df, df_IND[,c('Indicator','Indicator_Id')], by = 'Indicator', all = T)
drop = c("indicator")
df = df[ ,!(names(df) %in% drop)]

Step 4: Rescue the metadata from the hierarchy file and tokenize the Display.Name to make sure you can do correctly the left join later.

Hierarchy = read.csv("../Data preprocessed/hierarchy.indicators 12.31.17.csv")
#Hierarchy = read.csv("../Data preprocessed/GovData360IND.csv", sep = ";")
#colnames(Hierarchy)[5] = c('Display.Name')
Hierarchy = Hierarchy %>% filter(Dataset == Data_Source)
## Clean also df_IND / In this case it is needed
df_IND$Indicator = gsub(' rating', '', df_IND$Indicator)
df_IND$Indicator = gsub(' cluster average', '', df_IND$Indicator)
df_IND$Indicator = gsub('1low to 6high', '', df_IND$Indicator)
df_IND$Indicator = gsub(' -', '-', df_IND$Indicator)
df_IND$Indicator = gsub('policy for social inclusionequit', 'policies for social inclusion/equit', df_IND$Indicator)
df_IND$Indicator = gsub('CPIA ', '', df_IND$Indicator)
df_IND$Indicator = gsub('  ', ' ', df_IND$Indicator)
## Make similar Display.Name and Indicator
Hierarchy$Display.Name = gsub("_", "", Hierarchy$Display.Name)
Hierarchy$Display.Name = gsub("_", "", Hierarchy$Display.Name)
Hierarchy$Indicator = Hierarchy$Display.Name 
Hierarchy$Indicator = tolower(Hierarchy$Display.Name)
Hierarchy$Indicator = gsub("[[:punct:]]", "", Hierarchy$Indicator)
Hierarchy$Indicator = gsub(" topic average", "", Hierarchy$Indicator)  
Hierarchy$Indicator = gsub(" cluster average", "", Hierarchy$Indicator) 
Hierarchy$Indicator = gsub("social protection and labor","social protection", Hierarchy$Indicator) 
Hierarchy$Indicator = trimws(Hierarchy$Indicator, which = 'both')
Hierarchy = Hierarchy %>% mutate(Indicator = paste(tolower(Indicator), Dataset, "Total", sep = "-"))
print(Hierarchy)

The indicators that do not match is because they might be dropped in the past. In any case, we will bring them until the end. They will have the categories and some other columns empty in the final dataset. At the last minute, we will dropped them if it proceeds. Step 5: Left join between df_IND and Hierarchy.

Hierarchy = Hierarchy %>% select('Indicator', 'Display.Name', 'Value.Type.Slug','Value.Type.Descriptor', 'Units', 'Rank.1', "Category.1.1", "Category.1.2", "Category.1.3", "Category.1.4", "Category.1.5", "Rank.2", "Category.2.1", "Category.2.2", "Category.2.3", "Category.2.4", "Category.2.5", "Rank.3","Category.3.1", "Category.3.2", "Category.3.3", "Category.3.4", "Indicator.Code", "Indicator.ID")
Master_IND = merge(df_IND, Hierarchy, by.x = 'Indicator', by.y = 'Indicator', all.x = T)
# Drop and rename Display name. (In this case we will use the one in Hierarchy because it is cleaner)
drop = c('Display_Name')
